06/02/2011
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Five miners were killed on Saturday (February 5th) in an explosion in the Uricani coal mine in southwest Romania. 
The victims were working to fix a power transformer when the blast occurred. 
The mine employs about 800 employees. 
An investigation of the explosion is under way. 
(Agerpres, Realitatea, Mediafax, AFP - 05/02/11)
